The K-12 Cybersecurity Act has been signed into law to enhance the cybersecurity of K-12 educational institutions in the United States. This law emphasizes the importance of protecting sensitive information held by schools and aims to provide tools and guidance to secure their information systems. The global pandemic has highlighted the need to safeguard the sensitive information of students and educators, as well as all Americans. The law is seen as a significant step in addressing the ongoing threat posed by cybercriminals and adversaries. The Biden Administration is committed to a whole-of-nation effort to confront cyber threats and will continue to work on maintaining strong cybersecurity practices.